OL,3,CHospital's Chief Nurse apologises to
OL,4,Cfamilies unhappy with their maternity
OL,5,Ccare
OL,7,FOne of the most senior health leaders
OL,8,Fin Oxfordshire says she is "deeply
OL,9,Fcommitted" to delivering "safe, high
OL,10,Fquality, outstanding care" after more
OL,11,Fthan 500 families came forward to say
OL,12,Fthe John Radcliffe's maternity
OL,13,Fdepartment harmed them.
OL,15,FIn an exclusive interview with ITV
OL,16,FNews Meridian, Yvonne Christley, the
OL,17,FChief Nurse at Oxford University
OL,18,FHospitals Trust, said she has
OL,19,F"personally reviewed all the
OL,20,Ftestimonies, they make for a
OL,21,Fdistressing read."
